defaultWe would have hoped that most Councils would always follow any reasonable recommendation from the LGO to engage in mediated dispute resolution, at any stage in the LGO processes, including as the result of any challenge to any ruling, without requiring a formal Public Report, a court order or any statutory compulsion to do so.
